news.title: Fitch downgrades Evergrande & Kaisa after missed payment deadlines
news.para: The downgrades to so-called "restricted default" status come even though Evergrande and Kaisa have not officially announced defaults that could result in drawn-out debt restructuring processes.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group kicks off $12 billion debt restructuring: Source
news.para: Kaisa, China's largest holder of offshore debt among developers after China Evergrande Group, did not repay $400 million of bonds that matured on Tuesday, triggering cross-default provision on all its offshore bonds and prompting a downgrade to "restricted default" by Fitch Ratings.

news.title: Mumbai: HC frowns at Mhada lottery clause for Swan Mills workers
news.para: “Prima facie this does not appeal to us and needs to be rectified,” said Justices Gautam Patel and Madhav Jamdar on a petition by Girni Kamgar Sabha and nearly 50 allottees against Mhada’s June 20, 2012, circular that split Swan Mills into two codes for allotments.

news.title: Mohali civic body to use tiles, paver blocks made of construction waste
news.para: The plant has been made functional and was inspected by Mohali Mayor Amarjit Singh Sidhu alias Jeeti Sidhu on Wednesday. Sidhu said the MC has taken up various initiatives to bring Mohali at number one in the sanitation survey.

news.title: Parliamentary panel seeks details on status of Delhi master plan-2021
news.para: The committee, in its original report on the subject, had desired that the "high-level committee" of the DDA meet at periodic intervals for reviewing, monitoring and managing the master plan, so as to enable achieving the targets, the parliamentary panel said.

news.title: Maharashtra government planning police housing schemes: PWD minister
news.para: "The state government is devising various schemes in collaboration with CIDCO for providing housing and quarters for police personnel. Their housing issues need to be addressed even after they retire from service," the PWD Minister said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh to waive Rs 10,000 crore worth housing loans through OTS
news.para: The chief minister made this announcement with the officials during his review meeting on housing programme at his Tadepalli camp office on Wednesday.

news.title: Aurangabad civic body to waive off Rs 257 crore penalty of property tax defaulters
news.para: The Aurangabad Municipal Corporation on Wednesday announced 75% waiver on delayed payment charges for one-time settlement of the property tax by the defaulters.

news.title: Poor response to Nashik civic body's amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: Around 17,500 defaulters availed the scheme getting a rebate of Rs 56.33 lakh in penalty amount during the period. The NMC recovers 2% fine per month on tax dues from the last day of paying taxes.

news.title: Shriram Properties IPO sails through on Day 2 thanks to retail investors
news.para: Analysts are divided on the IPO. Some of them see the issue priced at comparatively very high valuations. Others believe that its growth opportunity compensates for that.

news.title: South Delhi civic body may give breather on property tax
news.para: The committee also aims to reduce the 1% education cess charged on annual/rateable value of property.

news.title: Telangana: Over 200 villas built sans nod, some on lake FTL in Dundigal
news.para: As many as 200 villas have been allegedly built illegally on the city's periphery in Mallampet village under Dundigal municipality. Of these, at least eight were built by encroaching five acres of full tank level (FTL) and buffer zone of Katwa cheruvu in the village.

news.title: Better.com CEO apologizes after laying off 900 employees via Zoom call
news.para: Vishal Garg, who has come under intense criticism after the SoftBank-backed company laid off about 9% of its workforce through the video call, said he had "blundered the execution" of communicating the layoffs.

news.title: Tata Realty to invest Rs 150 crore to develop Hailey Road project
news.para: The Hailey Road project will have about 100,000 sq. ft. of built-up area with 40 to 42 7-star luxury apartments with average size of 2000 sq ft.

news.title: Gurugram: Notice to 13 building sites in DLF-1 for flouting pollution norms
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) RS Batth said work at the construction sites was stalled after several violations, including uncovered building material at sites, were noted.
